s ATM network that reaches 70 cities and towns currently not linked to the private bank's network, BancoEstado chairman Jaime Estevez said. The connection should be operational in March 2003.   Start your 15 day free trial now!   Start a Free Trial  Already a subscriber? Please, login   Santander Chile maintains a churn rate of 5%, compared to 10% registered in the local financial system, as a result of product price and quality and despite the ongoing merger with fellow Chilean bank Santiago, Roccatagliata was quoted as saying.      Commercial & Retail Banking Mergers & Acquisitions                 Related Content      Company ProfileBanco Santander-Chile        Notes Create                              Close  E-mail to a Friend       Banking   Chile  Santander banks on product variety, marketing, distribution ByKeith Mackenzie - Wednesday, December 18, 2002     Name:    Enter email:     Your friend's e-mail address:    Add personalized message:             Send              Close  Unlock this content      We are sorry. You have no more credits available :(   0/News Your current credit balance is:   You have not added any company.days left until your credit is updated.          Subscribe                    Close  We have something new for you               Prev Next    Prev Next    Prev Next    Prev Next    Prev Next    Prev Close             Close  Create note             Company-wide    Private    250 characters available.         Need help? We have two types of notes: company-wide, that can be viewed by your whole team; and private, only by you.  Create note              Close  My notes        Search        Company-wide    Private       No hay notas  Load more     Create note                          Delete             July 22, 2017                                               BNamericas - Latin America's Business News, Information and Research Center for the Global Economy                                          About us   Contact    Store    Advertising   Cu