Home


About us:
Global network

DNB Chile - SantiagoTo Global networkThe Santiago branch opened in 2008 as the first Scandinavian international bank to focus on the seafood, shipping and energy sectors in Chile. We are currently staffed with 11 employees. The Santiago branch also covers other countries in Latin America, such as uruguay, Peru and others. Currently the Santiago Branch is performing as a financial institution.The branch serves local corporate customers within our main industry sectors, as well as Nordic and International Corporations based in Chile.

Established in 2008
11 employees
Focused on seafood and Project Finance
Servicing clients within selected industries, leveraging in-depth knowledge and industry-specific competence
Establishing and maintaining key client relationships at a senior level

DNB's activities in Chile are concentrated in the following core areas:Industry sectors

Energy
Seafood
Telecommunications
 Products and services

Lending
Structured Finance
Corporate Finance
